From: Jared Isaacman
Sent: Wednesday, December 11, 2019 4:21 PM
To: J.Resnick@shift4.com; abiederman@shift4.com

Adam and Jon,

Hope you are both doing well.

I know there are a lot of industry rumors out there and they probably made their way to you
that we are out shopping the business. For the record, they are true. We are getting pretty far
along with TA and another PE firm that many of you know. They are submitting LOIs by the end
of the week. I think either could be good partners for us on the next chapter.

I have some concerns with the Card Connect litigation. First, it’s taking a very long time and I
doubt we will see resolution before the end of Q1 and that will not look good alongside the
PE activity. Second, I was planning a big family vacation at the end of Q1 on the boat
somewhere and it looks like I am getting deposed in early April so that is going to conflict.
Third, and obviously most important, the cash on our balance sheet between the holdback,
fees and the overall cost of the litigation will be unacceptable.

My ask is simple. I want to put an end to all of this. My objective is to get the best possible
outcome here and 1 am willing to accept some risk to make it a quick resolution. I have no
interest in going through 2020 with this on the books.

We have a board call tomorrow. I obviously think it will be best to have an update to share.

As always, appreciate your help.

Jared

To: 'Senator Toomey
Subject:

Senator,

Happy New Year! I hope you and your family had a wonderful holiday. 

I know there are a million pressing matters going on both here and overseas so I will keep this very brief. I need a little
help on two items and I know you will know what to do.

First, I am working on my annual presentation to the Federal Reserve and it's always very well received. They often
ask me to present to the various Governors who oversee payments. I always put a great deal of effort into preparing
for this presentation and, of course, share my perspective from the front lines. I have attached last year's presentation
for your reference. I would really appreciate it if you can put in a good word for me at the Fed. I know you are very
close with all the Governors there. It would be great if they take my concerns seriously.

Second, I was hoping you could get me your autograph for a veteran I know. He sent me a text that I have copied
below. His name is Frank and I can ship the items to your office. I am only asking for this one veteran --- I do not
want to make a habit of this. I have a lot of asks all the time.

Frank: "Buddy, hey I hate to ask but my friends Dad served with our Senator Toomey and is dying of cancer from
agent orange. He would be happy to get a picture and autograph if you could ask for me."

Thanks again. Again, sorry to bother you with so much. I know you will give me good guidance.

Jared
